     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <p>T.D. Hexasticon, siue gratulatio <hi>in Theologicon R.H.</hi>
   </p>
   <q>
      <l>Cedite sectarum primates, cedite puri,</l>
      <l>Harueius patriae seruiet atque Deo.</l>
      <l>Non curat fatuos, nō christomastigas audit</l>
      <l>Non credit placitis principiis{que} nouis.</l>
      <l>Perge, liber, certa ingenii praedictio recti,</l>
      <l>Et patriae, &amp; populo, principibus{que} place</l>
   </q>
   <p>Vnio gemmarum Regina.</p>
   <epigraph>
      <q>
         <bibl>
            <hi>Mat. c.</hi> 9. <hi>v.</hi> 37, 38. <hi>Luke c.</hi> 10. <hi>v.</hi> 2.</bibl>
         <p>The haruest is great but the labourers are fevve, pray ye therefore the Lord of the haruest that he vvould sende more labou<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>rers into his haruest.</p>
      </q>
   </epigraph>
</div>
